hypothesis: EAD (expect-act-diff) anchors the observer and suppresses serendipitous null-result discovery (S190 dream-hypothesis)
method: Retrospective analysis of n=365 EAD-equipped entries across SWARM-LANES.md, NEXT.md, NEXT-ARCHIVE.md, SWARM-LANES-ARCHIVE.md. Categorized diff= fields into MATCHED/EXCEEDED/UNEXPECTED/FALSIFIED/NULL.
verdict: DROPPED — hypothesis refuted. EAD is a contrast generator, not a confirmation anchor. The 36-57% unexpected/falsified rate and increasing temporal trend are incompatible with anchoring-suppression. The 0% null-result rate is one valid sub-concern: survivorship bias or reframing of nulls as falsified.
